pull_request.title: Add SPDX-License-Identifier headers
pull_request.body:
Fixes #642.

Before merging:

- [ ] Update [coding conventions wiki page](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/wiki/Coding-conventions)

pull_request.title: Addresses #122
pull_request.body:
As discussed in #122  not a perfect solution but probably the best doable at this time.

Also fixes a (probable) memory de-allocation problem.

Only additional documentation: `openssl speed` and `openssl s_client/s_server` output in case of unsupported algorithms requested. CI testing not really doable as discussed in [the issue](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl/issues/122#issuecomment-624288897).

pull_request.title: Overhauled test suite.
pull_request.body: The speed tests have been temporarily taken out the CI. Once, `openssl speed` can parse OQS key-exchanges in the form of the names given [here](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl/blob/OQS-OpenSSL_1_1_1-stable/oqs-template/generate.yml#L3), a parallelized version of the KEM and SIG tests can be added to a nightly build.
